{
  "stem": "26699.2",
  "chunk_idx": 3,
  "model": "openai/gpt-oss-120b",
  "elapsed_s": 5.8,
  "sentences_input": [
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "And we ran to my grandmother's house.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 7,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "[PAUSES] The men were all cramped in the basements of the police, and they were locked up there.",
      "word_count": 18
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 0,
      "text": "For a number of days, we didn't know what was the fate of my father and others.",
      "word_count": 17
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 1,
      "text": "[PAUSES] So actually what happened was that out of the thousands of people who were there, [PAUSES] about 2000 or so were taken to the railway station and squashed in cattle [PAUSES] wagons.",
      "word_count": 33
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 2,
      "text": "The rest-- because there was no room in the train for all the thousands who were there-- were left to go home.",
      "word_count": 22
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 3,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 6 SECONDS] I didn't experience directly what happened with-- I read afterwards the terrible thing what happened when these people were suffocated in those wagons.",
      "word_count": 27
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 4,
      "text": "Amongst them was-- there were two of my uncles and other relatives.",
      "word_count": 12
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 5,
      "text": "[PAUSES] And they were taken for seven days without water and very little air and lots of rotten bodies in the big heat of the summer.",
      "word_count": 26
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 6,
      "text": "And most of them, they died the most terrible death possible.",
      "word_count": 11
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 7,
      "text": "Some of them, they lost their mind.",
      "word_count": 7
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 8,
      "text": "And fortunately, my uncle, David, who now lives in Argentina, survived together with other couple of hundreds out of the thousands who were there.",
      "word_count": 24
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 9,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 5 SECONDS] All in all, I was told by my parents that about 14,000 people were murdered on that particular day and the days after in the train.",
      "word_count": 30
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 10,
      "text": "[PAUSES FOR 6 SECONDS] My memories are very sharp and clean from these days.",
      "word_count": 14
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 11,
      "text": "[PAUSES] And I can say one thing, that in one day, I matured.",
      "word_count": 13
    },
    {
      "segment_idx": 8,
      "sentence_idx_in_seg": 12,
      "text": "[PAUSES] I understood what it means that you have to control yourself to hide, to protect your life and the life of others at the age of six.",
      "word_count": 28
    }
  ],
